# Marketing section patterns

The marketing site lives in `src/components/marketing/`. Compose the homepage from these sections in `src/app/page.tsx`. Always follow the shared scaffold below — it is what gives the site its visual rhythm.

## Section scaffold

Every section is its own component, exports a named function, no default export, server-renderable when possible.

```tsx
export function PaymentsSection() {
  return (
    <section className="relative py-20 sm:py-28 overflow-hidden">
      {/* Optional backdrop layer */}
      <div className="absolute inset-0 bg-grid opacity-30 pointer-events-none" />
      <div className="absolute -top-32 right-1/3 h-72 w-72 rounded-full bg-amber-soft blur-3xl opacity-60 pointer-events-none" />

      <div className="relative max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6">
        {/* content */}
      </div>
    </section>
  );
}
```

Rules:

- Vertical rhythm: `py-20 sm:py-28`. Hero gets `pt-24 sm:pt-32`.
- Outer container: `max-w-7xl mx-auto px-4 sm:px-6`. **Do not** widen.
- Backdrops are `absolute inset-0 pointer-events-none`. Use `bg-grid`, `bg-wash`, or a single soft `blur-3xl` color blob.

## Eyebrow + display title

Open every section with the same header rhythm:

```tsx
<span className="pill">
  <CreditCard className="h-3 w-3" />
  Payments
</span>
<h2 className="mt-5 font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl tracking-tight leading-[1.05] text-ink">
  Connect any
  <br />
  <span className="display-italic text-emerald-brand">payment processor.</span>
</h2>
<p className="mt-5 text-base sm:text-lg text-foreground/70 leading-relaxed max-w-md">
  Subhead. Two sentences max. End with a sharp claim.
</p>
```

- Pill variants: `.pill` (emerald), `.pill-amber`, `.pill-clay`. For hero / pricing use `<span className="pill pill-amber">// pricing · per property</span>`.
- The italic accent is **mandatory** on H2s — it carries the brand voice.
- Body copy uses `text-foreground/70` (never `text-gray-*`) and `max-w-md` / `max-w-2xl` to keep measure tight.

## Two-column feature layout (copy + visual)

Use `grid lg:grid-cols-12` and split 5/7. Copy left, visual right.

```tsx
<div className="grid lg:grid-cols-12 gap-10 lg:gap-12 items-center">
  <div className="lg:col-span-5">{/* eyebrow + h2 + bullets + CTAs */}</div>
  <div className="lg:col-span-7">{/* card-elev showcase */}</div>
</div>
```

Bullets pattern (icon badge + title + body):

```tsx
{POINTS.map((p) => {
  const Icon = p.icon;
  return (
    <div key={p.title} className="flex items-start gap-3">
      <span className="inline-flex h-9 w-9 rounded-lg bg-emerald-soft text-emerald-brand items-center justify-center shrink-0">
        <Icon className="h-4 w-4" strokeWidth={2} />
      </span>
      <div className="leading-snug">
        <p className="font-medium text-ink text-[15px]">{p.title}</p>
        <p className="text-sm text-foreground/65 mt-1 max-w-md">{p.body}</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  );
})}
```

## Showcase card (right column)

Wrap content in `card-elev p-6 sm:p-8`. Inside, build a mini-product preview:

1. Header row: small mono label + display title + animated `live` pill.
2. Grid of mini-tiles (`grid grid-cols-2 sm:grid-cols-3 gap-3`) with `card-surface`-style inner blocks: small icon badge, label, mono confirmation line.
3. Code/terminal block — `bg-ink text-[#f1ebde] rounded-xl p-5 font-mono text-[12px]`. Comments in `text-amber-soft`, type names in `text-emerald-soft`.
4. Stats trio at the bottom: three `card-surface` chips with mono eyebrow + `.numeral` value.

This is the formula behind the Payments and LivePreview sections — reuse it for any new feature highlight.

## CTAs in sections

Pair primary + secondary, always rounded-full, side by side:

```tsx
<div className="mt-8 flex flex-wrap items-center gap-3">
  <Link href="/demo" className="group inline-flex items-center justify-center gap-2 h-11 px-5 rounded-full bg-emerald-brand text-primary-foreground font-medium hover:bg-ink transition-colors">
    Try the checkout
    <ArrowRight className="h-4 w-4 transition-transform group-hover:translate-x-0.5" />
  </Link>
  <Link href="/dashboard/payments" className="inline-flex items-center justify-center h-11 px-5 rounded-full border border-[color:var(--border)] bg-card text-ink font-medium hover:bg-surface transition-colors">
    View admin
  </Link>
</div>
```

Section-level CTA copy is direct, single verb-led: "Try now", "Try the checkout", "Talk to sales". Avoid "Learn more" / "Click here".

## Mobile

- Stack columns at `lg:` breakpoint.
- Drop one type step on mobile (`text-4xl sm:text-5xl`, `py-20 sm:py-28`).
- Horizontal scrollers (Kanban, marquees): wrap with `overflow-x-auto scrollbar-none` and `snap-x snap-mandatory` if appropriate.

## Page composition

`src/app/page.tsx` order is intentional and shouldn't be reshuffled without reason:

```
<Navbar />
<Hero />
<LanguagesMarquee />
<HowItWorks />
<LivePreview />
<Features />
<PaymentsSection />
<Audiences />
<Stats />
<PricingTeaser />
<CTA />
<Footer />
```

When adding a new section, place it after the closest topical sibling and follow the same scaffold above — that is what keeps the page coherent.
